# GameNative — Game Launch, Invites & Notifications

## 1. Root cause of the "black screen / no game" bug

Wine's `winex11.drv` uses Xlib/XCB to connect to the X server.
On Linux, XCB **always probes the abstract-namespace socket first**:
`\0/tmp/.X11-unix/X0`  (sun_path[0] = '\0').
If that fails it falls back to the filesystem path `/tmp/.X11-unix/X0`.

GameNative's X server used to bind only the filesystem socket at
`rootDir/tmp/.X11-unix/X0`.  The guest process is NOT chrooted, so
`/tmp` is the real Android `/tmp`, not `rootDir/tmp`.  Neither path
Wine tried matched — winex11.drv failed, no window was created.

**The root fix (already implemented):**

`XConnectorEpoll` now ALSO binds the abstract-namespace socket
`\0/tmp/.X11-unix/X0` when `socketConfig.abstractSocketName != null`.

- `UnixSocketConfig.createSocket(rootPath, XSERVER_PATH, true)` — pass
  `useAbstractNamespace = true` to enable this for the X server socket only.
- `xconnector_epoll.c` — `createAbstractAFUnixSocket(name)` creates the
  abstract fd; `doEpollIndefinitely` reads the `abstractServerFd` field via
  JNI and calls `accept()` on either server fd when each fires.
- `abstractServerFd` field on `XConnectorEpoll` must be `package-private`
  (or at minimum readable via `GetFieldID`) so the JNI helper can read it.

**DO NOTs for the X server socket:**
- Do NOT try to use `redirect.conf` or `REDIRECT_CONFIG` env vars as a
  workaround — libredirect does not rewrite `/tmp` based on those vars.
- Do NOT add a `chroot` or bind-mount — requires root, breaks portability.
- Do NOT put `XSERVER_PATH` / `.X11-unix` paths anywhere except
  `UnixSocketConfig.java` and the native JNI layer.
- Do NOT remove the abstract-namespace socket binding without providing an
  equivalent fix; it is the only rootless way to make winex11.drv connect.

---

## 2. X server socket setup rules

- Only ONE place creates the X server socket:
  `XServerScreen.kt` calls `UnixSocketConfig.createSocket(rootPath, XSERVER_PATH, true)`.
  Both call sites (lines ~1764 and ~1992) must use `useAbstractNamespace = true`.
- All other sockets (ALSA, PulseAudio, SYSVSHM, VirGL, STEAM_PIPE, VORTEK)
  use the default `createSocket(rootPath, path)` — **no abstract namespace**.
- The abstract socket name is the verbatim relative path (`/tmp/.X11-unix/X0`),
  NOT the imagefs-absolute path.  Xlib expects exactly that name.

---

## 3. Env-var rules for the guest process (`BionicProgramLauncherComponent`)

| Variable | Value | Reason |
|---|---|---|
| `DISPLAY` | `:0` | Wine display selection |
| `ROOT` | `rootDir.getPath()` | Used by libredirect for known path rewrites |
| `TMPDIR` | `rootDir + "/usr/tmp"` | Guest temp files |
| `ANDROID_SYSVSHM_SERVER` | `rootDir + SYSVSHM_SERVER_PATH` | Shared memory socket |

- Do NOT set `REDIRECT_CONFIG` or `REDIRECT_CONF` — libredirect ignores them.
- Do NOT set `WINEDEBUG` in non-debug builds (kills CPU performance).
- Do NOT set `DXVK_HUD` in production builds.

