## 7. In-game side panel (swipe right-to-left)

The panel is `NavigationDialog` shown on back-button press.

**Current items:**
1. Keyboard (ACTION_KEYBOARD = 1)
2. Input Controls (ACTION_INPUT_CONTROLS = 2)
3. Edit Controls (ACTION_EDIT_CONTROLS = 4)
4. Edit Physical Controller (ACTION_EDIT_PHYSICAL_CONTROLLER = 5) — conditional
5. Exit Game (ACTION_EXIT_GAME = 3)

**Add:**
6. Steam Invites (ACTION_GAME_INVITES = 6) — only when `pendingInviteCount > 0`
   - Show a badge overlay on the icon with the pending invite count.
   - Tapping launches `InviteListDialog` (or a Compose overlay pushed over XServerScreen).

**Rules for NavigationDialog:**
- Keep the grid layout; do NOT switch to a list layout.
- Do NOT add more than 2 new items without also restructuring the grid for readability.
- Icon tint must use `R.color.navigation_dialog_item_color` (same as all others).
- Use `Bricolage Grotesque Regular` font for all labels (already applied via `R.font.bricolage_grotesque_regular`).

---

## 8. Launch error screen

When Wine exits with non-zero status (status=137 = OOM/killed, status≠0 = crash):
- Show a dark error card on top of the black XServerScreen.
- Display: exit status code, last relevant Wine log lines (from `wine_output.log`),
  and a "Report / Copy Log" button.
- Do NOT auto-dismiss; the user must explicitly tap "Exit" or "Retry".
- Retry re-calls `PluviaApp.xEnvironment?.startEnvironment()` without destroying the container.

---

## 9. General rules (restate for this context)

- Outfit font only — never Inter, Roboto, or `sans-serif`.
- Steam blue `#1E9FFF` for primary actions; never purple/violet.
- No light backgrounds in any component in this file.
- No card elevation drop shadows — use `strokeColor` border (`#FFFFFF18`).
- All new Kotlin files in `app/src/main/java/app/gamenative/` must follow the
  existing package structure (`ui/component/`, `ui/screen/`, `ui/model/`, `events/`).
